Static fields/Class variables: Fields that are associated with class.

Final:
------
public class Constants{
    public static final int SPEED_OF_SOUND = 343;
}

Static initilization block:
---------------------------
- Used to perform some gloabl checks or initilize static variables.

static {
    currentModelNb = 10;
}


Static nested class:
---------------------
A top level class that has been nested in another top  level class for convenience.

Private static nested class: Used for serialization
-----------------------------
public class A{
    private List<Entry> entries = new ArrayList<>();

    private static class Entry{
        private string x;
        private Entry(){
            this.x = x;
        }
    }
}

public static nested classes:

public class A{
    private List<Entry> entries = new ArrayList<>();
    
    public static class Entry{
        private string x;
        private Entry(){
            this.x = x;
        }
    }
}

A.Entry x = new A.Entry(m);